# ingredients/

PNG art for each herb, one file per entry in data/herbs.json.

Filename convention: herb name lowercased, apostrophes stripped, spaces hyphenated.
- "chamomile"        -> chamomile.png
- "black pepper"     -> black-pepper.png
- "cat's claw"       -> cats-claw.png
- "st johns wort"    -> st-johns-wort.png

Image spec:
- Format: PNG, transparent background
- Dimensions: 88x100 (2x the rendered 44x50 slot for retina sharpness)
- Subject: clean botanical illustration or photograph of the herb itself
- Sourcing: public-domain botanical illustrations (Köhler's Medizinal-Pflanzen,
  Sturm's Flora, Wikipedia Commons) preferred; CC-licensed photos acceptable
  if author attribution is acknowledged in a SOURCES.md alongside.

Renderer falls back to an invisible slot if a PNG is missing, so partial
population is safe.
